My name is Konstantin, and I'm 35 years old. 
I was born in Krasnoyarsk, Russia. I have always had a passion for swimming, running  as my hobbies. 
In terms of education, I attended the university in Krasnoyarsk, where I studied economics, finance, and credit.

Professionally, I have 8 years of experience in various fields. 
I initially worked in a construction company, where I gained valuable insights into the building industry and project management. 
Following that, I transitioned to Rosneft, where I worked in the tax department, handling financial records and ensuring compliance with tax regulations. 

I have a strong interest in frontend development and I'm currently pursuing studies to become a frontend developer. 
I find immense satisfaction in creating visually appealing and user-friendly websites and applications. 
It allows me to combine my passion for technology with my creative problem-solving skills.

In my free time, I enjoy spending quality time with friends, 
particularly outdoors, exploring nature, and engaging in activities such as hiking or picnicking. 
Additionally, I have a deep love for travel, 
which allows me to immerse myself in different cultures, broaden my perspective, and create unforgettable memories.
